09/05/2011
ATHENS, Greece -- A makeshift mosque was torched early Sunday (May 8th) causing property damage but no injuries.
Investigators say arsonists broke a window of a flat that is used for religious practices in the district of Kallithea.
Local media reported a Nazi swastika was painted on windows.
(Ta Nea, To Vima, Nafthemporiki - 08/05/11)
